edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.device
Class PIPRouteThrough

java.lang.Object
  edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.device.PIPRouteThrough
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class PIPRouteThrough
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

This class is used to represent the Route-Through constructs of XDLRC/XDL in association with PIPs. Certain PIPs are defined as special configurations of logic blocks which allow routing to pass through them. This class defines these kinds of routing constructs.

Author:
Chris Lavin
